## Add a New Dashboard Page

- Create both files:
  - `demo-app/app/(dashboard)/<route>/page.tsx`
  - `demo-app/app/(dashboard)/<route>/_components/<FeaturePageComponent>.tsx`
- Use PascalCase for React components. Default export in `page.tsx` is `<Feature>PageComponent`.
- Import only via absolute alias `@/*`.
- Compose the page with `AppSidebar` and render the feature component in `main`.

### Template

```tsx
// demo-app/app/(dashboard)/<route>/page.tsx
import { AppSidebar } from "@/components/app-sidebar"
import { <FeaturePageComponent> } from "@/app/(dashboard)/<route>/_components/<FeaturePageComponent>"

export default function <Feature>Page() {
  return (
    <div className="flex h-screen bg-background">
      <AppSidebar />
      <main className="flex-1 overflow-auto">
        <<FeaturePageComponent> />
      </main>
    </div>
  )
}
```

```tsx
// demo-app/app/(dashboard)/<route>/_components/<FeaturePageComponent>.tsx
"use client"

export function <FeaturePageComponent>() {
  return (
    <div className="p-6">{/* content */}</div>
  )
}
```

### Example: Settings

- `demo-app/app/(dashboard)/settings/page.tsx` uses `SettingsPageComponent` from `_components`.
- If adding a new Settings shell page, include:
  - `demo-app/app/(dashboard)/settings/page.tsx`
  - `demo-app/app/(dashboard)/settings/_components/SettingsPageComponent.tsx`

### Sidebar

- To expose a new route, add to `demo-app/components/app-sidebar.tsx` navigation.

### Do/Don't

- Do: PascalCase components, absolute imports, colocate feature components in `_components`.
- Don't: Use relative imports, snake_case component names, or place feature UI outside its page folder.
